description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you either an&lt;br /&gt;• accredited counsellor or psychotherapist AND a registered nurse/AHP/medic with experience in the acute hospital environment? &lt;br /&gt;• OR a registered counselling psychologist with experience working in an acute hospital environment?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Chelsea based Band 7 0.8wte Oncology Counsellor or Counselling psychologist to work in our ‘exploratory’ pathway (e.g. integrative, existential, person centred and psychodynamic approach). As well as inpatient and outpatient work, this role will also include supervision to nurses/ AHPs within the trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be joining a supportive and friendly team of qualified and trainee psychological practitioners from across a range of clinical backgrounds, including art therapy, counselling, psychology (clinical and counselling), psychosexual therapy, psychotherapy, psychiatry and mental health nursing. There is good internal and external CPD provision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We encourage you to contact us to discuss the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameJustin GrayerJob titleConsultant PsychologistEmail addressjustin.grayer@rmh.nhs.ukTelephone number020 7808 2777&lt;/p&gt;
